timeline.bodyText:
I've thought about having the retreaters have a getChanges() method that returns a list of change objects.  These change objects would encapsulate the retreatSameTerritoryUnits, retreatOtherTerritoryUnits, and extraRetreatChange logic.  But I didn't think the existing Change objects fit this.  The HistoryNode objects are kind of a good fit since these "changes" already create history nodes but HistoryNode doesn't seem to have actions to perform.
The api of this "change" object would be something like:
interface BattleChange {
  void writeHistoryNode();
  Change perform();
}

And perform would build the actual Change objects as well as modify the BattleState (if needed).

